cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with modeling and control of traffic flow in road networks, which involves the use of dynamic systems and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.MA (Machine Learning) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence and neural networks, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper's focus on nonlinear phenomena and emergent network dynamics suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant sub-category.
